Interface Function3Async<T1,​T2,​T3,​R>

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Function3AsyncSupport, Function3ToFunction3Async
    public interface Function3Async<T1,​T2,​T3,​R>
    A Function3Async is a reference to a function with return value that can be invoked asynchronously in another thread. With Function3Async it is possible to track the status and outcome using the FunctionAsyncResult returned upon invocation or by defining a Consumer as callback for the invocation.
    Author:
    tilmann

      • beginApply

        FunctionAsyncResult<R> beginApply​(java.util.function.Consumer<? super FunctionAsyncResult<R>> callback,
                                  java.lang.Object asyncState,
                                  T1 parameter1,
                                  T2 parameter2,
                                  T3 parameter3)
        Asynchronously invoke this Function3Async with the given parameter value, callback and asyncState.

        Associated with each call to beginInvoke is a FunctionAsyncResult instance returned by the call and given to the callback that can be used to track the status and outcome of the invocation.

        Parameters:
        callback - the Consumer, if given to beginInvoke, is invoked upon completion of the Function3Async's invocation and receives the same FunctionAsyncResult that is returned by the call to beginInvoke.
        asyncState - the asyncState is an arbitrary reference that, if given to beginInvoke, can be retrieved from this invocations FunctionAsyncResult.getAsyncState()
        parameter1 - the first parameter's value for the invocation
        parameter2 - the second parameter's value for the invocation
        parameter3 - the third parameter's value for the invocation
        Returns:
        the FunctionAsyncResult associated with this asynchronous invocation
